16/11/2010
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police arrested on Monday (November 15th) a man suspected of committing genocide in Srebrenica. 
Dragan Crnogorac, 38, was detained in Banja Luka based on a request by BiH's Prosecution Office. 
About 8,000 Bosniak men and boys were killed by Bosnian Serb forces in Srebrenica in July 1995. 
(B92, Tanjug, BN TV, Nezavisne Novine - 15/11/10)
